- ✅ `[GeneratedRegex]` used for .NET 7+ with `RegexOptions.Compiled` fallback for older TFMs — good dual-targeting
- ✅ `Concat(char, ReadOnlySpan<char>)` uses `stackalloc` — zero-heap helper (though unused at L106 where it should be)
- ✅ `string.Contains(char)` used at L61 — ordinal, no issue
- ✅ No `new Regex()` per-call, no `.Substring()` calls

